The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for predicting properties of molecules, which falls under the domain of computational chemistry. The paper proposes a new unsupervised representation for molecules, which can be used with supervised learning methods for prediction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of the paper.
